INFO:dev_server:Trace: {
  "name": "AzureChatOpenAI",
  "context": {
    "trace_id": "55dbd18e37b9ed052d616e9e043083ab",
    "span_id": "59ba9694e490c44f"
  },
  "parent_id": "7a9e13e8bcd91813",
  "start_time": 1767443854061815040,
  "end_time": 1767443866479476992,
  "attributes": {
    "input.value": "{\"messages\": [[{\"lc\": 1, \"type\": \"constructor\", \"id\": [\"langchain\", \"schema\", \"messages\", \"HumanMessage\"], \"kwargs\": {\"content\": \"Market trends in 2025\", \"type\": \"human\"}}]]}",
    "input.mime_type": "application/json",
    "output.value": "{\"generations\": [[{\"text\": \"Here are some high-level market trends that many analysts expect to shape 2025. This is a broad, not-transactional view and depends on policy, geopolitics, and how quickly the global economy adapts to new tech and energy dynamics.\\n\\nMacro backdrop\\n- Inflation and interest rates: The path of inflation and central-bank policy will be a major driver. If inflation remains contained and growth holds up, rate cuts or a slower pace of hikes could support higher asset valuations. If inflation proves stickier, real yields stay higher and risk assets could face headwinds.\\n- Growth vs. upside surprises: A \u201csoft landing\u201d scenario with productivity gains (e.g., from automation and AI) could support modestly higher growth without fueling runaway inflation. Conversely, a sharper slowdown or policy misstep could weigh on equities and credit.\\n- AI and productivity: Widespread AI adoption and automation should boost productivity and capex efficiency in many sectors, favoring technology, software, semiconductors, data-center services, and adjacent industries (cybersecurity, compute hardware).\\n- Green transition and energy: Investment in renewables, grid modernization, EVs, energy storage, and critical minerals will influence energy and materials markets. This can support certain cyclicals (infrastructure, industrials) and commodity prices (copper, lithium, nickel) while changing long-run energy equities.\\n- Geopolitics and supply chains: Ongoing diversification of supply chains, tech decoupling considerations, and regulatory tensions (antitrust, data, cross-border data flows) could keep volatility elevated and create opportunities in areas like defense, cybersecurity, and specialized manufacturing.\\n\\nAsset-class themes\\n- Equities\\n  - Growth vs. value rotation: Technology and AI-linked names may continue to lead, but there could be renewed rotation into higher-quality, cash-flow-rich businesses across sectors.\\n  - Sector balance: Tech and healthcare may benefit from productivity themes; energy and materials could perform when commodity cycles improve; consumer-oriented stocks depend on income dynamics.\\n  - Regional stocks: The US and parts of Europe may diverge in performance based on inflation dynamics, earnings visibility, and policy signals; Asia (ex-Japan) could gain from cyclical growth and export demand if trade conditions improve.\\n- Fixed income\\n  - Duration: With inflation outcomes uncertain, active management and duration positioning will be important. Investment-grade credits may offer balance between yield and risk, while longer-duration bets depend on inflation trajectories.\\n  - Spreads and quality: Credit spreads may widen in risk-off environments but compress in growth or tech upcycles. Focus on high-quality, cash-flows and defensively positioned issuers.\\n- Commodities and real assets\\n  - Energy transition metals: Copper, lithium, nickel, cobalt could be more sensitive to capex cycles and policy incentives.\\n  - Oil and gas: Prices will hinge on demand growth, supply discipline, and geopolitics; energy equities often react to price moves.\\n  - Real assets: Infrastructure and real estate with inflation linking or long-term leases can offer diversification and inflation hedging.\\n- Currencies and rates\\n  - Currency impact: Currency gains or losses will depend on relative inflation and growth across regions; hedging considerations may be important for cross-border portfolios.\\n  - Rates regime: A \u201chigher-for-longer\u201d vs. \u201clower-for-longer\u201d environment will guide diversi\ufb01cation between cash, Treasuries/govies, and credit.\\n\\nRisks to watch\\n- Policy missteps: If inflation proves stickier or if central banks tighten aggressively late, markets could reprice risk assets sharply.\\n- Geopolitical shocks: Trade tensions, sanctions, or conflicts could disrupt supply chains and commodity prices.\\n- Financial discipline: High corporate leverage or sizable maturity walls in certain sectors could amplify volatility in a downturn.\\n- Economic growth surprises: Faster-than-expected growth could lift rates and equities; slower growth could depress valuations and risk assets.\\n\\nTactical ideas (broad)\\n- Focus on quality: Companies with strong balance sheets, pricing power, and cash flow resilience tend to perform better in uncertain environments.\\n- Diversify by region and sector: Use a mix of growth, quality, defensives, and selective cyclicals to weather different regimes.\\n- Thematic exposure: Consider tilt toward AI/automation, cybersecurity, healthcare innovation, and energy-transition beneficiaries, with careful stock/issuer selection.\\n- Inflation and rate sensitivity: Build a balance between equities, high-quality fixed income, and inflation-linked or real assets to manage real return risk.\\n- Active vs passive: In 2025, active management can help navigate evolving sectors, volatility, and idiosyncratic risks; core passive exposure for broad market exposure remains useful.\\n\\nWould you like me to tailor this to a specific region, asset class, or time horizon (e.g., US equities, European fixed income, Asia-Pacific growth, or a retirement-focused strategy)? If you share your region, risk tolerance, and whether you\u2019re looking for long-horizon investing or shorter-term positioning, I can provide a more focused view.\", \"generation_info\": {\"finish_reason\": \"stop\", \"logprobs\": null, \"content_filter_results\": {\"hate\": {\"filtered\": false, \"severity\": \"safe\"}, \"protected_material_code\": {\"detected\": false, \"filtered\": false}, \"protected_material_text\": {\"detected\": false, \"filtered\": false}, \"self_harm\": {\"filtered\": false, \"severity\": \"safe\"}, \"sexual\": {\"filtered\": false, \"severity\": \"safe\"}, \"violence\": {\"filtered\": false, \"severity\": \"safe\"}}}, \"type\": \"ChatGeneration\", \"message\": {\"lc\": 1, \"type\": \"constructor\", \"id\": [\"langchain\", \"schema\", \"messages\", \"AIMessage\"], \"kwargs\": {\"content\": \"Here are some high-level market trends that many analysts expect to shape 2025. This is a broad, not-transactional view and depends on policy, geopolitics, and how quickly the global economy adapts to new tech and energy dynamics.\\n\\nMacro backdrop\\n- Inflation and interest rates: The path of inflation and central-bank policy will be a major driver. If inflation remains contained and growth holds up, rate cuts or a slower pace of hikes could support higher asset valuations. If inflation proves stickier, real yields stay higher and risk assets could face headwinds.\\n- Growth vs. upside surprises: A \u201csoft landing\u201d scenario with productivity gains (e.g., from automation and AI) could support modestly higher growth without fueling runaway inflation. Conversely, a sharper slowdown or policy misstep could weigh on equities and credit.\\n- AI and productivity: Widespread AI adoption and automation should boost productivity and capex efficiency in many sectors, favoring technology, software, semiconductors, data-center services, and adjacent industries (cybersecurity, compute hardware).\\n- Green transition and energy: Investment in renewables, grid modernization, EVs, energy storage, and critical minerals will influence energy and materials markets. This can support certain cyclicals (infrastructure, industrials) and commodity prices (copper, lithium, nickel) while changing long-run energy equities.\\n- Geopolitics and supply chains: Ongoing diversification of supply chains, tech decoupling considerations, and regulatory tensions (antitrust, data, cross-border data flows) could keep volatility elevated and create opportunities in areas like defense, cybersecurity, and specialized manufacturing.\\n\\nAsset-class themes\\n- Equities\\n  - Growth vs. value rotation: Technology and AI-linked names may continue to lead, but there could be renewed rotation into higher-quality, cash-flow-rich businesses across sectors.\\n  - Sector balance: Tech and healthcare may benefit from productivity themes; energy and materials could perform when commodity cycles improve; consumer-oriented stocks depend on income dynamics.\\n  - Regional stocks: The US and parts of Europe may diverge in performance based on inflation dynamics, earnings visibility, and policy signals; Asia (ex-Japan) could gain from cyclical growth and export demand if trade conditions improve.\\n- Fixed income\\n  - Duration: With inflation outcomes uncertain, active management and duration positioning will be important. Investment-grade credits may offer balance between yield and risk, while longer-duration bets depend on inflation trajectories.\\n  - Spreads and quality: Credit spreads may widen in risk-off environments but compress in growth or tech upcycles. Focus on high-quality, cash-flows and defensively positioned issuers.\\n- Commodities and real assets\\n  - Energy transition metals: Copper, lithium, nickel, cobalt could be more sensitive to capex cycles and policy incentives.\\n  - Oil and gas: Prices will hinge on demand growth, supply discipline, and geopolitics; energy equities often react to price moves.\\n  - Real assets: Infrastructure and real estate with inflation linking or long-term leases can offer diversification and inflation hedging.\\n- Currencies and rates\\n  - Currency impact: Currency gains or losses will depend on relative inflation and growth across regions; hedging considerations may be important for cross-border portfolios.\\n  - Rates regime: A \u201chigher-for-longer\u201d vs. \u201clower-for-longer\u201d environment will guide diversi\ufb01cation between cash, Treasuries/govies, and credit.\\n\\nRisks to watch\\n- Policy missteps: If inflation proves stickier or if central banks tighten aggressively late, markets could reprice risk assets sharply.\\n- Geopolitical shocks: Trade tensions, sanctions, or conflicts could disrupt supply chains and commodity prices.\\n- Financial discipline: High corporate leverage or sizable maturity walls in certain sectors could amplify volatility in a downturn.\\n- Economic growth surprises: Faster-than-expected growth could lift rates and equities; slower growth could depress valuations and risk assets.\\n\\nTactical ideas (broad)\\n- Focus on quality: Companies with strong balance sheets, pricing power, and cash flow resilience tend to perform better in uncertain environments.\\n- Diversify by region and sector: Use a mix of growth, quality, defensives, and selective cyclicals to weather different regimes.\\n- Thematic exposure: Consider tilt toward AI/automation, cybersecurity, healthcare innovation, and energy-transition beneficiaries, with careful stock/issuer selection.\\n- Inflation and rate sensitivity: Build a balance between equities, high-quality fixed income, and inflation-linked or real assets to manage real return risk.\\n- Active vs passive: In 2025, active management can help navigate evolving sectors, volatility, and idiosyncratic risks; core passive exposure for broad market exposure remains useful.\\n\\nWould you like me to tailor this to a specific region, asset class, or time horizon (e.g., US equities, European fixed income, Asia-Pacific growth, or a retirement-focused strategy)? If you share your region, risk tolerance, and whether you\u2019re looking for long-horizon investing or shorter-term positioning, I can provide a more focused view.\", \"additional_kwargs\": {\"refusal\": null}, \"response_metadata\": {\"token_usage\": {\"completion_tokens\": 1990, \"prompt_tokens\": 12, \"total_tokens\": 2002, \"completion_tokens_details\": {\"accepted_prediction_tokens\": 0, \"audio_tokens\": 0, \"reasoning_tokens\": 960, \"rejected_prediction_tokens\": 0}, \"prompt_tokens_details\": {\"audio_tokens\": 0, \"cached_tokens\": 0}}, \"model_provider\": \"openai\", \"model_name\": \"gpt-5-nano-2025-08-07\", \"system_fingerprint\": null, \"id\": \"chatcmpl-CtvAWdwt3wTJF0OEBLNxNYKpjHrOT\", \"prompt_filter_results\": [{\"prompt_index\": 0, \"content_filter_results\": {\"hate\": {\"filtered\": false, \"severity\": \"safe\"}, \"jailbreak\": {\"detected\": false, \"filtered\": false}, \"self_harm\": {\"filtered\": false, \"severity\": \"safe\"}, \"sexual\": {\"filtered\": false, \"severity\": \"safe\"}, \"violence\": {\"filtered\": false, \"severity\": \"safe\"}}}], \"finish_reason\": \"stop\", \"logprobs\": null, \"content_filter_results\": {\"hate\": {\"filtered\": false, \"severity\": \"safe\"}, \"protected_material_code\": {\"detected\": false, \"filtered\": false}, \"protected_material_text\": {\"detected\": false, \"filtered\": false}, \"self_harm\": {\"filtered\": false, \"severity\": \"safe\"}, \"sexual\": {\"filtered\": false, \"severity\": \"safe\"}, \"violence\": {\"filtered\": false, \"severity\": \"safe\"}}}, \"type\": \"ai\", \"id\": \"lc_run--019b83dc-f2ee-7f40-8dd2-d1cb064d25e2-0\", \"usage_metadata\": {\"input_tokens\": 12, \"output_tokens\": 1990, \"total_tokens\": 2002, \"input_token_details\": {\"audio\": 0, \"cache_read\": 0}, \"output_token_details\": {\"audio\": 0, \"reasoning\": 960}}, \"tool_calls\": [], \"invalid_tool_calls\": []}}}]], \"llm_output\": {\"token_usage\": {\"completion_tokens\": 1990, \"prompt_tokens\": 12, \"total_tokens\": 2002, \"completion_tokens_details\": {\"accepted_prediction_tokens\": 0, \"audio_tokens\": 0, \"reasoning_tokens\": 960, \"rejected_prediction_tokens\": 0}, \"prompt_tokens_details\": {\"audio_tokens\": 0, \"cached_tokens\": 0}}, \"model_provider\": \"openai\", \"model_name\": \"gpt-5-nano-2025-08-07\", \"system_fingerprint\": null, \"id\": \"chatcmpl-CtvAWdwt3wTJF0OEBLNxNYKpjHrOT\", \"prompt_filter_results\": [{\"prompt_index\": 0, \"content_filter_results\": {\"hate\": {\"filtered\": false, \"severity\": \"safe\"}, \"jailbreak\": {\"detected\": false, \"filtered\": false}, \"self_harm\": {\"filtered\": false, \"severity\": \"safe\"}, \"sexual\": {\"f